			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p139862">Direwolf Totem of Spirit</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=139862#p139862"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=369">sunamae</a></strong> &raquo; Jun 30th, '08, 15:23 </p>

			

			<div class="content">I was noticing a while ago that when I forget to use <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=53688" class="postlink">Direwolf Totem of Spirit</a> for the effect of <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=11518" class="postlink">Arcane Wolf Familiar</a> I get somewhat pounded into elf goo.  Are people who have upgrades to the mana effect using those or using the totem anyway?  I could see it being quite situational based on your personal danger.  But, what I see on lucy tells me that this stacks just fine with Improved Dodge.  Though I don't know if chance to dodge is hardcapped or anything. <br /><br />Sunamae<br />7th Hammer<br /><br />PS if you don't have this item yet and are 70+, get it!  I soloed it no problem using monster rogue hide/sneak and charm soloing the kill parts.</div>

			

		</div>

		
