			<h3 ><a href="#p139864">Re: Direwolf Totem of Spirit</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=139864#p139864"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5919">Disp</a></strong> &raquo; Jun 30th, '08, 16:12 </p>

			

			<div class="content">I got this a few months ago and was pretty excited about it, but after using it for a while I think this item is almost totally worthless. The problem with the familiar is twofold; it has hit points somehow, and they are super low (1 AE from about anything). This means that  any mob or raid that has an AE will smoke this thing in the first round no matter what, and then you're stuck with nothing. The other problem is you can't have a charmed pet or a regular pet while the familiar is active, so it's completely worthless in the most practical situation we would need it, soloing (unless the bug deal is still active, but I've never been able to figure out how to have the familiar up with a charmed pet/regular pet).<br /><br />My understanding is that it will stack with Dodge mods though. It's nice to have for very situational uses, but as a general rule it's not very useful. May as well get it though cause yeah the quest took me all of like an hour or hour and a half. Honeslty I rarely use it because in groups and raids I have too many other things to deal with that recasting this thing over and over after every fight is not a high priority, and I usually just forget...go for a clicky mana regen item from Crystallos IMO.</div>

			

		</div>

		
