	<div id="p141336" class="post bg1">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p141336">Re: Direwolf Totem of Spirit</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=141336#p141336"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4819">Moriquend</a></strong> &raquo; Dec 1st, '08, 15:31 </p>

			

			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>Lyrik Mindlethe wrote:</cite>Interesting...so I get 16% dodge with this item AND my assistant researcher's neck.  Now THAT's worth it.</div></blockquote><br /><br />It's not actually 16%.  The effects are...<br /><br />Assistant Researcher's Symbol - Skill mod: Dodge +8%, which raises your Dodge skill by 8%.<br />Arcane Wolf Familiar - Increase Chance to Dodge by 20%.<br />Improved Dodge IV (chosen because it is the best readily available level of the effect) - Increase Chance to Dodge by 40%.<br /><br />An 8% increase in Dodge Skill does not necessarily increase your chance of dodging an attack by 8%.  It may be more.  It may be less.  In any case, all three types of effects do, in fact, stack.  One is a Skill mod, another is a Worn mod, and the other is a Spell-based mod.  So, yes, it is very much worth it if you are being physically attacked by a mob.<br /><br />Here's something to ponder, though...<br />Does the effect from the Warrior Disc: Commanding Voice, actually stack with the Arcane Wolf Familiar effect seeing as how both are Spell-based mods, or do you only get the highest bonus of the two (in this case they are equal, so it could be either one) while you have both effects up?  Lucy does not show any stacking issues with the dodge portion of the Arcane Wolf Familiar effect and the only stacking issue shown for Commanding Voice is with the Guardian Circle line of clicky auras.</div>

			

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile141336">
			<dt>
				<a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4819">Moriquend</a>
